  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel offers a daily buffet breakfast serving hot and cold options, setting you up nicely for a good day's skiing.</p>
<p>In the evening, after a social drink in the bar, you'll be served a three-course meal made up of typical dishes from the area. On New Years Eve there's also a gala dinner.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Holiday Debili is on the cobbled shopping streets of <a data-udi="umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887}" title="Sauze d'Oulx">Sauze d'Oulx</a>. Its central position means you're just moments away from the shops, restaurants and bars around the resort. It's also only 100 metres from the Clotes lift too, giving you quick and easy access to the vast ski area.</p>
<p>The hotel itself has a traditional alpine interior. Have a drink each evening in the cosy bar whilst chatting over a game of pool. Rooms are classic but spacious, they are clean and tidy and have everything you need. There's a a great sauna on the 5th floor with amazing view and a small relaxation area.</p>
<p>Like with most family-run hotels in Italy, you can expect good, hearty Italian meals. The Debili family have been perfecting their recipes for almost 100 years. Their experience also stretches out to their service so you can expect to be well looked after during your stay.</p>]]></description>
